definitions.definition: Synonym of rich : the wealthy people of a society or of the world collectively .
examples: The wealthy pay most of the taxes but the uberwealthy hardly pay any at all: they hold stock and property and live off debt borrowed against that collateral.
F. Scott Fitzgerald never got over Ginevra King 's dad reminding him he wasn't a wealthy and needed to aim lower.

main_definition: ( plural only ) Synonym of rich : the wealthy people of a society or of the world collectively .
